# Forensic OSINT-to-Evidence Pipeline (FOEP)

[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue.svg)](https://python.org)

FOEP is a novel framework that integrates **digital forensics** and **open-source intelligence (OSINT)** into a unified evidence-handling system. Traditional tools in these domains often operate in isolationâ€”either focusing on internal breach artefacts or external intelligence. FOEP bridges this gap by correlating logs, memory dumps, and disk artefacts with social media traces, leaked databases, and other publicly available intelligence sources.

## âœ¨ Key Features

- **Unified Evidence Model**: Normalizes forensic and OSINT data into a consistent schema
- **Graph-Based Correlation**: Links entities across datasets using Neo4j
- **Credibility Scoring**: Dynamically ranks intelligence by reliability and corroboration
- **Legal Compliance**: Generates court-admissible reports with automated redaction
- **Chain of Custody**: Tracks provenance and integrity for all evidence
- **Modular Architecture**: Supports extensible ingestion, correlation, and reporting

## ðŸš€ Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- Neo4j 5+ (for graph correlation)
- System dependencies for `dfvfs` (see [dfvfs installation](https://github.com/log2timeline/dfvfs#installation))

### Installation

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/foep.git
cd foep

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv foep-env
source foep-env/bin/activate  # Linux/macOS
# foep-env\Scripts\activate   # Windows

# Install core dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install spaCy model (optional, for name redaction)
python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm

# Install development dependencies (optional)
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt

# Install Neo4j
wget -O - https://debian.neo4j.com/neotechnology.gpg.key | sudo apt-key add -
echo 'deb https://debian.neo4j.com stable 5' | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/neo4j.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y neo4j

# Start Neo4j
sudo systemctl start neo4j

# Set password via http://localhost:7474 (default: neo4j/neo4j)



Basic Investigation Workflow

# Create investigation directory
mkdir -p investigations/case-001
cd investigations/case-001

# Step 1: Ingest Evidence
foep-ingest \
  --log /path/to/logfile.log \
  --disk /path/to/disk.img \
  --memory /path/to/memory.raw \
  --social "github:username" \
  --social "twitter:handle" \
  --breach "email@domain.com" \
  --code "filename:.env password" \
  --output evidence.json \
  --case-id "CASE-001" \
  --investigator "Your Name"

# Step 2: Correlate Evidence
foep-correlate \
  --input evidence.json \
  --output correlated.json \
  --case-id "CASE-001" \
  --investigator "Your Name"

# Step 3: Generate Report
foep-report \
  --input correlated.json \
  --output reports/ \
  --case-id "CASE-001" \
  --investigator "Your Name" \
  --title "Investigation Report" \
  --description "Forensic analysis summary" \
  --format pdf
